Dar es Salaam &mdash; Former mariner Captain Ibrahim Bendera will be releasing his new book, 'Admiralty and Marinetime Law in Tanzania' tomorrow. The book, which is about Maritime Law in Tanzania is expected to be launched on by the former Prime Minister Judge (rtd) Sinde Warioba at the Dar es Salaam Maritime Institute (DMI). This was said in a press statement by the Marine Law Association of Tanzania.Among other things the book highlights issues of labor relations in the industry, harbors and ports. It also examines ship businesses like the carriage of goods and passengers by the sea which is regarded as the essence of maritime law by the experienced sailor-turned-legal-practitioners.Captain Bendera has combined the knowledge of his practical work as a ship captain and law knowledge on the maritime relations.